    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I'm finally getting around to rewriting my <a href=\"https://juliaregistries.github.io/General/packages/redirect_to_repo/TreatmenPanels\">TreatmenPanels.jl</a> package using <a href=\"https://juliaregistries.github.io/General/packages/redirect_to_repo/AxisKeys\">AxisKeys.jl</a> thanks to this thread. It's going reasonably well, albeit the documentation is a little... sparse.</p>\n<p>The main issue I'm having is that a lot of the API seems to be based around kwargs, and I'm not sure how to deal with this in cases where the dimension names are stored in variables. Generally my package will have an observation identifier and a time identifier, something like <code>data(id = \"Peru\", t = Date(2022))</code>. But I want the names of the dimensions to be given by users, i.e. I have a function <code>make_data(matrix, id_var, t_var)</code> which someone might call with <code>make_data(some_data, \"country\", \"year\")</code>. </p>\n<p>I've found the function <code>rekey</code> but that just changes the actual keys of a dimension, not the name of the dimension. I tried poking around in the internals a bit and it appears the dimension names are encoded in the type of the <code>NamedDimsArray</code> that's part of the <code>KeyedArray</code>, so I'm wondering if what I'm trying to do just isn't supported?</p>",
        "id": 553395341,
        "sender_full_name": "Nils",
        "timestamp": 1762180269
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One workaround would be to splat kwarg tuples like <code>data(; (id_var =&gt; \"Peru\", t_var =&gt; Date(2022))...)</code> but that seems a bit hacky</p>",
        "id": 553396130,
        "sender_full_name": "Nils",
        "timestamp": 1762180462
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I consider splatting kwargs more a normal thing than hacky. But if you prefer you can splat from a dictionary or any collection of two-element members. (The keys need to be symbols though.)</p>",
        "id": 553400906,
        "sender_full_name": "Gunnar Farnebäck",
        "timestamp": 1762181602
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Fair enough, I'll go down that route then, thank you.</p>",
        "id": 553401347,
        "sender_full_name": "Nils",
        "timestamp": 1762181715
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah sorry I missed the bit about keys having to be symbols - is that a general restriction of <code>AxisKeys</code>?</p>",
        "id": 553405112,
        "sender_full_name": "Nils",
        "timestamp": 1762182496
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't know anything about <code>AxisKeys</code> but keyword argument names must be symbols.</p>",
        "id": 553407004,
        "sender_full_name": "Gunnar Farnebäck",
        "timestamp": 1762182955
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, splatting is the way to go in this scenario. If names aren't known in compiletime, there'll be a dynamic dispatch, but this is fundamentally unavoidable – the type of the result differs anyways.</p>",
        "id": 553415070,
        "sender_full_name": "aplavin",
        "timestamp": 1762184613
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So, either <code>data(; (id_var =&gt; \"Peru\", t_var =&gt; Date(2022))...)</code> or <code>data(; NamedTuple{(id_var, t_var)}(\"Peru\", Date(2022))...)</code> depending on what fits best.</p>",
        "id": 553415286,
        "sender_full_name": "aplavin",
        "timestamp": 1762184671
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or <code>data(\"Peru\", Date(2022))</code> of course, if you can rely on the axis order.</p>",
        "id": 553415570,
        "sender_full_name": "aplavin",
        "timestamp": 1762184734
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah yes I can rely on the order, as I don't allow users to create the <code>KeyedArray</code> themselves and afaiu this can't be changed after construction</p>",
        "id": 553416220,
        "sender_full_name": "Nils",
        "timestamp": 1762184885
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, axis assignment is immutable</p>",
        "id": 553416733,
        "sender_full_name": "aplavin",
        "timestamp": 1762185000
    }
]